replies.body:
Caitlyn was reworked to be a "siege marksman"to be fair, that's her identity now

Varus and cork are played more as AD casters than ADCs, like a xerath, ziggs or lux

ADCs meaning auto attack, crits with ats speed and such

As for spellvamp, Riot said mages and adcs have different play styles which is why one has life steal while spell vamp is so exclusive. A mage (normally) is longer range or have their damage in bursts. Those who don't (Vlad cass Ryze) have plenty of healing, whats basically life steal for a mage (case e) or a shield when their burst is ready (ryze passive)

 Also, the reason mages have slightly harder build paths is that they're abilities are more impacting and their items do unique things, such as 
1. percent health burn {{item:3151}} 
2. slows {{item:3116}} 
3. zhonyas {{item:3157}} 
4. ludens {{item:3285}} 
5. are mr reduction {{item:3001}} 
6. spell blade {{item:3100}} 
7. mana shield with mana ap scaling {{item:3003}} {{item:3040}} 
8. stacking over time of health mana and AP{{item:3027}} 
9. AP on hit {{item:3115}} 
10. percent missing mana region {{item:3174}} 
11. grievous wounds{{item:3165}} 
12. and finally (something AD does not have at all) Full magic penetration, (not bonus) {{item:3135}} 

Now Ad items have some of these things, but at a cost like {{item:3036}} {{item:3033}}, all adcs would prefer the former but sometimes must give it up for the latter

AP Item / AD Equivalent
> 1. percent health burn {{item:3151}} / {{item:3153}} (% health damage, faster, scales better)
> 2. slows {{item:3116}} / {{item:3022}} 
> 3. zhonyas {{item:3157}} / {{item:3139}} 
> 4. ludens {{item:3285}} / {{item:3087}} 
> 5. are mr reduction {{item:3001}} / {{item:3071}} 
> 6. spell blade {{item:3100}} / {{item:3078}}  or {{item:3025}} 
> 7. mana shield with mana ap scaling  {{item:3040}} / {{item:3155}} or {{item:3072}} 
> 8. stacking over time of health mana and AP{{item:3027}} / {{item:3071}} (without all that pesky stacking over time + penetration and CDR)
> 9. AP on hit {{item:3115}} / Every single item
> 10. percent missing mana region {{item:3174}} / {{item:3508}}  
> 11. grievous wounds{{item:3165}} / {{item:3123}} 
> 12. and finally (something AD does not have at all) Full magic penetration, (not bonus) {{item:3135}} 
13.  Free Assassination Buff  AP No Item / AD {{item:3147}} 
14.  Free AOE Attacks  AP ... / AD {{item:3085}}  or {{item:3074}}  
15.  Bonus Range  AP ... / AD {{item:3094}} 
16.  Reduce Enemy Damage by Flat %  AP ... / {{item:3046}}
